Norway’s Giske Backs Private Investments for Oil Fund, DN Says

-- B y   S t e p h e n   T r e l o a r
-- 
2011-05-12T06:21:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/norway-s-giske-backs-private-investments-for-oil-fund-dn-says.html
Industry Minister Trond Giske
supports a change in the mandate for  Norway ’s sovereign-wealth
fund to allow investments in unlisted companies, Oslo-based
Dagens Naeringsliv reported, citing the minister.  The fund, which is administered by the  Finance Ministry  and
manages Norway’s oil revenue, is restricted to investing in
publicly listed companies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Treloar at 
 streloar1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  